(3. COMPLETED WORKFLOW) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CUSTOMER ORDERING WORKFLOW) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Customer opens the menu page.) Tj
T*
(2. Customer browses menu categories and items.) Tj
T*
(3. Customer clicks Add to cart.) Tj
T*
(4. The system gives visible feedback that the item was added.) Tj
T*
(5. Customer reviews cart contents.) Tj
T*
(6. Customer chooses either:) Tj
T*
(   - Cash at counter) Tj
T*
(   - Stripe payment) Tj
T*
(7. If counter is selected:) Tj
T*
(   - Order is created immediately) Tj
T*
(   - Payment status remains unpaid) Tj
T*
(8. If Stripe is selected:) Tj
T*
(   - Order is created first) Tj
T*
(   - Customer is redirected to Stripe Checkout) Tj
T*
(   - After successful payment, the order is marked paid) Tj
T*
(9. Customer returns to the success page.) Tj
T*
(10. Customer can later view the order in their dashboard and download a voucher.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(ADMIN OPERATIONS WORKFLOW) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
