(4. PAYMENT WORKFLOW) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(COUNTER PAYMENT) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(? Customer places order) Tj
T*
(? Order is created with payment status unpaid) Tj
T*
(? Staff can later mark it paid from admin dashboard) Tj
T*
(? Paid orders are counted in business reporting only after payment status is updated) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(STRIPE PAYMENT) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(? Customer selects Stripe payment) Tj
T*
(? Backend creates the order first) Tj
T*
(? Backend creates Stripe Checkout Session) Tj
T*
(? Customer pays on Stripe Checkout page) Tj
T*
(? Stripe redirects customer to success page) Tj
T*
(? Stripe webhook confirms successful payment) Tj
T*
(? Backend marks the related order as paid automatically) Tj
T*
(? Paid Stripe orders appear correctly in admin reporting) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. REPORTING LOGIC) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The reporting page has been designed so that only paid orders contribute to recognized) Tj
T*
(income. This is important for business accuracy.) Tj
ET
